This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing dynamic textures. It also involves feature extraction and classification, which are common tasks in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as slow feature analysis (SFA) and manifold regularization, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). 

Additionally, the paper involves video-level representation and dynamic scene recognition, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
